reviews.review: Muy buena para ser el final viniendo de los giros inesperados del 8
Loved it!  Got the real star wars feeling when all the ships come flying in and the galaxy is ready to stand up.

This is an EPIC closure for the Star Wars Saga, extremely emotional and with several potent moments which ties perfectly the three trilogies of Star Wars. The cast is just perfect, with awesome action sequences and some great shots. The Rise of Skywalker when it bets, bets HIGH and at the very end it pays very well.
Enjoyed this from beginning to end. So much fun tying up all the lose ends.
Amazing end to the story! it's a must see!

Rey isn't as much of a mary sue no more but the plot is much to in your face. The ending was good but was hard to follow. The whole movie all adds up to thirty minutes. Till then its just small interesting things every thirty minutes. I personally thought it was better than the other two so that's why im giving it three point five stars. I was content watching it not blown away or did I have a grasp of nostalgia.
Disney has made me question my fandom. I would see it again though
Rise of Skywalker is a decent sci-fi movie, but watching it continuously fan service every scene possible made it feel like a fanfic or a video game plot

I had purchased the tickets a couple of months ago, wanted to be at one of the first showings of the final episode, if for no other reason than sentimentality .... a little surprised that the theatre was far from sold out and that there was no "special moment" vibe, at all.  The showtime was supposed to be 9:30,  it started at 10:05 ... subjected to nearly 55 minutes of over-modulated marketing.  As the movie progressed, just had this feeling was something was missing.  At times, the special effects felt like I was in star wars version of the Matrix.  The storyline felt worn & weary, I've seen this show before - although Daisy Ridley was good.  See it, but don't be surprised if you're underwhelmed and a little disappointed as the credits roll.
I just finished watching the movie and I thought it was the perfect ending to the Skywalker saga!
